def knn_predict(X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test, k):
    y_hat_test = []

    for test_point in X_test:
        distances = []

        for train_point in X_train:
            distance = Mahanttan(test_point, train_point)
            distances.append(distance)
        # print(distance)
        
        # Simpan data dalam bentuk data frame
        df_dists = pd.DataFrame(data=distances, columns=['dist'], 
                                index=y_train.index)
        
        # Urutkan jarak, dan hanya pertimbangkan k titik terdekat
        df_nn = df_dists.sort_values(by=['dist'], axis=0)[:k]

        # buat objek counter untuk melacak label k tetangga terdekat
        counter = Counter(y_train[df_nn.index])

        # Dapatkan label paling umum dari semua tetangga terdekat
        prediction = counter.most_common()[0][0]
        
        # ubah prediksi ke menjadi list
        y_hat_test.append(prediction)
        
    return y_hat_test

from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
def plot_complexity_curve(k_list, knn_model, X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test):
    
    train_scores = []
    test_scores = []
    
    # For each k
    for k in k_list:
        # Initialize, fit, predict
        knn = knn_model(k)
        
        knn.fit(X_train, y_train)
        
        train_scores.append(knn.score(X_train, y_train))
        test_scores.append(knn.score(X_test, y_test))

    # Plot
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    
    ax.plot(k_list, train_scores, label='Training Accuracy', color='red')
    ax.plot(k_list, test_scores, label='Testing Accuracy', color='black')

    ax.set(title='k-NN with Different Values for $k$',
           xlabel='Number of Neighbors',
           ylabel='Accuracy')
    
    ax.legend()
    
neighbors = np.arange(1, 15)
plot_complexity_curve(neighbors, KNeighborsClassifier, X_train, X_test, Y_train, Y_test)
